# AI Slop Eradication

**When writing docs, comments, or summaries:** Cut the slop. Be direct.

## Banned (or use sparingly)

| Slop | Use instead |
|------|-------------|
| utilize | use |
| leverage (as verb) | use, apply — or drop |
| facilitate | let, enable, support |
| enhance | improve, add |
| optimize | improve, tune — or say what |
| comprehensive | full, complete — or drop |
| holistic | — (usually drop) |
| robust | solid, or say what |
| seamlessly | — (drop) |
| empower | enable, let |
| streamline | simplify |
| scalable / scalability | scales, or "more engineers" |
| cutting-edge / state-of-the-art | — (drop or say what) |
| synergy / synergies | — (drop) |
| paradigm | model, approach |
| ecosystem | (when technical: Cargo, npm — ok; when filler: drop) |
| in order to | to |
| it's worth noting / important to note | — (just state it) |
| dive into / dive deep | look at, check |
| our team / our organization | we, or drop |
| at the end of the day | — (drop) |
| game-changer | — (say what changed) |
| happy to help / feel free to | — (or "Ask.") |

## Voice

- **Short.** Bullets over paragraphs.
- **Active.** "We ship" not "It is shipped."
- **Concrete.** "Rust, SSDF, SBOM" not "industry best practices."
- **No throat-clearing.** "Why it matters" not "Why This Matters for [Company]."

## Exception

Technical terms (MOSA, SSDF, SBOM, CMMC) and Kova voice ("We do difficult," "Realize the impossible") — keep. Those aren't slop.

